# Get Cooking — New Project Setup Wizard

When the user says **"Get cooking"** (or variations like "get cooking", "let's cook", "start cooking"), begin the tiered setup wizard.

## Before Starting

1. Read the master setup recipe: `docs/ai/recipes/setup-new-project.md`
2. Read the current environment: `.env.example`, `frontend/config/app.ts`, `frontend/config/fonts.ts`
3. Read `FORK-ME.md` for context on what Sourdough provides

## Step 1: Welcome & Orient the User

**Before asking any tier questions**, present this to the user:

### Wizard Overview

Greet the user and explain the setup process conversationally. Cover these points:

> "Let's get your project set up! This is a **3-tier wizard** — I'll ask you some questions, make the changes, and then you can decide if you want to keep going or pause and come back later."

Present the wizard outline so the user knows what to expect:

| Tier | Focus | What Happens |
|------|-------|-------------|
| **1. Identity & Branding** | Name, colors, fonts, logo | Renames "Sourdough" everywhere, sets your look & feel |
| **2. Features & Auth** | Which features to keep, auth model | Removes what you don't need, configures login |
| **3. Infrastructure & Repo** | Database, ports, git setup | Configures the runtime and prepares the repo |

Tell them: *"You can stop after any tier and pick up where you left off later. Each tier takes effect immediately, so your app is usable after every step."*

### Quick Tips

Then share the Quick Tips so the user knows the key shortcuts from the start. Present these conversationally using the "just say..." tone:

**Releasing code:**

| Just say | What happens |
|----------|-------------|
| **"push"** | Commits all changes, bumps patch version, tags, and pushes |
| **"push minor"** | Same but bumps minor version (new feature set) |
| **"push major"** | Same but bumps major version (breaking change) |
| **"push — added user dashboard"** | Uses your message as the commit message |

**Planning features:**
- Say **"Add ___ to the roadmap"** — I'll create a plan file and track it
- Say **"Work on ___"** — I'll load the plan and start building
- Say **"What's on the roadmap?"** — I'll review what's active, next, and planned

**Building things:**

| Just say | What I'll do |
|----------|-------------|
| "Add an API endpoint for widgets" | Follow the API endpoint recipe |
| "Add a config page for my feature" | Follow the config page recipe |
| "Add a dashboard widget for stats" | Follow the dashboard widget recipe |
| "Review my code" | Run the full code review checklist |

There are **36 step-by-step recipes** — you don't need to know which one, just describe what you want.

**How I work:** This codebase is built for AI-assisted development. I automatically load context, follow tested recipes, run code reviews, and keep docs updated.

### Then proceed

After presenting the overview and Quick Tips, say: **"Ready to start with Tier 1?"** and wait for confirmation before proceeding to the Tier 1 questions below.

