## Tier 2: Features & Auth

**Ask these questions next:**

1. **Which features to keep?** Present as a checklist (defaults = keep all):
   - [ ] AI/LLM integration (multi-provider, 3 orchestration modes)
   - [ ] Notification channels — which ones? (Email, Telegram, Discord, Slack, SMS, Matrix, ntfy, Web Push, In-App)
   - [ ] Backup/restore — which destinations? (Local, S3, SFTP, Google Drive)
   - [ ] PWA (installable app, offline support)
   - [ ] Full-text search (Meilisearch)
   - [ ] HIPAA/access logging (warn: this is woven into core middleware — removal is deeper surgery)

2. **Auth model?** Each tier builds on the previous:
   - Email/password only (simplest)
   - \+ SSO (adds OAuth login buttons)
   - \+ 2FA (adds TOTP + recovery codes)
   - \+ Passkeys (adds WebAuthn/FIDO2 passwordless login)
   - Default: Email/password + optional SSO

3. **Which SSO providers?** (only if SSO selected): Google, GitHub, Microsoft, Apple, Discord, GitLab

**After collecting answers → execute `docs/ai/recipes/setup-features-auth.md`**

